    "body": "@DataMonk2017  If this is what I think it is ( A usage question for changing `df` index names) I'd like you to refer to the `df.rename` feature.\r\nOne example which could be useful for you : \r\n```python\r\ndf = pd.DataFrame([[0,1,\"Foo\"],[\"bar\",2,3]], columns = [\"yo\",\"vo\",\"zo\"], index=[\"lol\",\"zol\"])\r\n>>> df\r\n      yo  vo   zo\r\nlol    0   1  Foo\r\nzol  bar   2    3\r\n\r\ndf.rename(index = {'lol' : 'red'}, inplace=True)\r\n      yo  vo   zo\r\nred    0   1  Foo\r\nzol  bar   2    3\r\n``` "
